  Publisher                = {ACM},
  Series                   = {SCG '08},

  Abstract                 = {In recent years a considerable amount of work in graphics and geometric optimization used tools based on the Laplace-Beltrami operator on a surface. The applications of the Laplacian include mesh editing, surface smoothing, and shape interpolations among others. However, it has been shown [13, 24, 26] that the popular cotangent approximation schemes do not provide convergent point-wise (or even L2) estimates, while many applications rely on point-wise estimation. Existence of such schemes has been an open question [13].

